race.comment: YEAH BUDDY (1) is third-up and ready to fire in easier company. Maps for a soft run and the longer sprint is sure to suit. HELLO DOLLY DIVA (5) resumes and just missed at Toowoomba on debut. She will be naturally improved and should get every chance. MISHANI VISION (9) didn't get into it at Ipswich but missed a whisker at Toowoomba prior over 1000m. Has to manage an outside barrier but she arrives at peak fitness and expect a much better effort. SWANFELS (11) raced over 1400m at Eagle Farm on debut and settled last in an 11-horse field after missing the kick. She'd won a Deagon trial prior and is better suited at this level. Draws wide but we should see more from her with the extra race fitness and learning.
